<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="323" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="323">
The original description is brief, and characters needed to properly place this species are largely absent. We interpret &quot;from upper margin of the frontal depression and because there is no ridge connecting the latter to anterior ocellus&quot; to refer to a carinate margin of the frontal depression, as is seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Hadronotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hadronotus ancinla" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancinla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Hadronotus ancinla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.8.e47687" author="Chen, H" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" refId="B35" refString="Chen, H, Talamas, EJ, Bon, M-C, Moore, MR, 2020. Gryon ancinla Kozlov &amp; Le (Hymenoptera: Scelionidae): host association, expanded distribution, redescription and a new synonymy. Biodiversity Data Journal 8: e47687. https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.8.e47687" title="Gryon ancinla Kozlov &amp; Le (Hymenoptera: Scelionidae): host association, expanded distribution, redescription and a new synonymy. Biodiversity Data Journal 8: e 47687." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.8.e47687" year="2020">Chen et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
), and which may be connected to the anterior ocellus by a carina. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mineo, G" journalOrPublisher="Phytophaga" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" pagination="17 - 28" refId="B182" refString="Mineo, G, 1992. New species of Gryon Haliday (Hym. Scelionidae). Phytophaga 4: 17 - 28" title="New species of Gryon Haliday (Hym. Scelionidae)." volume="4" year="1992">Mineo (1992)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName family="Scelionidae" genus="G." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. fervidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" rank="species" species="fervidum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">G. fervidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Gryon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gryon hiberus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiberus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Gryon hiberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but the description of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Gryon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gryon hiberus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiberus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Gryon hiberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mineo, G" journalOrPublisher="Frustula Entomologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" pagination="47 - 59" refId="B179" refString="Mineo, G, 1990b. Studies on the Scelionidae (Hym, Proctotrupoidea) XXVI. Material for a revision of Gryon Hal. with description of a new species: Gryon risbeci. Frustula Entomologica 12: 47 - 59" title="Studies on the Scelionidae (Hym, Proctotrupoidea) XXVI. Material for a revision of Gryon Hal. with description of a new species: Gryon risbeci." volume="12" year="1990 b">Mineo (1990b)</bibRefCitation>
is also brief and insufficient for generic placement. We examined the holotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Hadronotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hadronotus lucmon" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucmon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Hadronotus lucmon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Gryon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gryon lucmon" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucmon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Gryon lucmon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
concomitantly with 
<taxonomicName family="Scelionidae" genus="G." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. fervidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" rank="species" species="fervidum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">G. fervidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was also placed in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Talamas &amp; Bremer &amp; Moore &amp; Bon &amp; Lahey &amp; Roberts &amp; Combee &amp; McGathey &amp; van Noort &amp; Timokhov &amp; Hougardy &amp; Hogg" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Gryon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gryon hiberus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiberus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Gryon hiberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and which belongs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Hadronotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hadronotus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Hadronotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our examination of a paratype specimen also supports placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Scelionidae" genus="Hadronotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hadronotus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="323">Hadronotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
